---
import CaseStudy from "../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro";

const metrics = [
  { value: "40+", label: "Users migrated" },
  { value: "<1 week", label: "Full adoption" },
  { value: "7 years", label: "Data preserved" },
];
---

<CaseStudy
  title="CRM migration and sales process redesign — Poliglota"
  tag="EdTech · Internal operations"
  metrics={metrics}
>
  <section>
    <h2>Context</h2>
    <p>
      Poliglota had built its own internal CRM. Over time, maintaining it was
      pulling engineering resources away from the core product — the learning
      experience.
    </p>
    <p>
      I led the migration to HubSpot, making sure data was preserved and all
      teams could adopt the new system quickly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Engineering effort going into a non-core tool</li>
      <li>Scalability limits in the internal CRM</li>
      <li>7 years of commercial data that could not be lost</li>
      <li>Different teams needed different parts of the customer journey</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Discovery</h2>
    <p>
      I mapped the full lead lifecycle and worked with the commercial team,
      customer service, and data analytics to understand what each team needed.
    </p>
    <p>
      Key finding: not everything should move to HubSpot. Some processes needed
      to stay inside Poliglota's platform.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Solution</h2>
    <p>I designed a two-system ecosystem.</p>
    <div class="flow">
      <div class="flow-item">
        <span class="flow-label">HubSpot</span>
        <h3>Commercial operations</h3>
        <p>
          Lead capture, qualification, pipeline management, and deal tracking.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-item">
        <span class="flow-label">Poliglota platform</span>
        <h3>Student lifecycle</h3>
        <p>Student onboarding, post-sale support, and coach coordination.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>My role</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Workflow Mapping</li>
      <li>Stakeholder Management</li>
      <li>Requirement Gathering</li>
      <li>Data Migration Coordination</li>
      <li>Future-State Process Design</li>
      <li>Adoption Planning</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Results</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>20–25 sales team members migrated to HubSpot</li>
      <li>~15 customer service users migrated</li>
      <li>Full adoption in less than one week</li>
      <li>Less manual coordination between teams</li>
      <li>Engineering resources freed from CRM maintenance</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Key learning</h2>
    <p>
      Good product decisions are sometimes about what not to build. Knowing when
      to use an external tool instead of building internally is part of the
      strategy.
    </p>
  </section>
</CaseStudy>
